Important Day of DPRK Observed Abroad 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 4 (KCNA) -- A seminar on the Songun politics was held in Karachi of Pakistan, a lecture at the Kim Jong Il Library in Tanzania and a photo exhibition and a film show by the Laos-Korea Tin Company between Jan. 23 and 26 to celebrate the birthday of Kim Jong Il.
 Displayed in the venue of the photo exhibition were pictures showing the personality of Kim Jong Il as a great man. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the film show watched the Korean film "Mt. Paektu, Spirit of Korea." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman and the secretary general of the Society for the Study of Self-Reliance of Pakistan at the seminar explained in depth the root, features, validity, and great vitality of the Songun politics. They stressed that the DPRK would advance the human cause of independence to victory, repulsing the high-handed and arbitrary practices of the imperialists, under the banner of Songun in the future, too. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The deputy secretary of the Coast Regional Committee of the Revolutionary Party of Tanzania in the lecture stated that the exploits performed by Kim Jong Il for global independence would be everlasting. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The director of the Laos-Korea Tin Company said that looking around the photos on display, he came to know better about the popular traits of Kim Jong Il. The Korean people led by him will build a great, prosperous and powerful nation in near future, he added.

Int'l Preparatory Committee Formed to Mark February 16 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 4 (KCNA) -- The International Alliance of the Eastern European and Central Asian Regional Association for the Study of the Juche Idea and the Songun Politics inaugurated an international preparatory committee for celebrating February 16 and adopted a resolution on it in Sankt-Peterburg, Russia, on January 27.
 The committee consists of members of parliaments from different countries in the region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chiefs and representatives of Juche idea study organizations in the region held a seminar on Internet to significantly celebrate February 16, the birthday of Kim Jong Il, the resolution noted, and said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We agreed that a body sponsoring the celebration events is needed to activate the work of disseminating the Juche idea and the Songun politics, and decided to form the International Preparatory Committee for Celebrating February 16 with the international alliance as an umbrella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We reached an agreement in views that it is especially important for the countries in Eastern Europe and Central Asia to introduce the experiences of the DPRK in line with their specific conditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One of the main political aims of the committee is to foil the imperialists' moves to stifle the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Acknowledging the necessity and urgency to introduce the Juche idea and the Songun politics in accord with realities, we are going to draw and execute a unified plan to conduct a more active study and dissemination of Kim Jong Il's works on the Juche idea on the occasion of February 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Thai Preparatory Committee for Celebrating February 16 was formed on Jan. 29. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the Organization for the Study of the Juche Idea of Thailand and the chairman of the Thailand-Korea Friendship Association were elected co-chairmen of the preparatory committee.

Meeting for Reunification and Progress Held in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 4 (KCNA) -- A meeting of officials of the South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification (Pomchonghakryon) was reportedly held in Seoul from Jan. 23 through 24 to accelerate the struggle for reunification in 2007.
 The speakers at the meeting underlined the need to foil the U.S. moves for sanctions and war against the DPRK through a struggle for peace against the U.S. and war and escalate the struggle to throw overboard the Grand National Party, a war party dead-set against national reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A declaration of struggle of the South Headquarters of Pomchonghakryon for this year was read out at the meeting, which said that the youth and students would turn out in the struggle to implement the three-point task of attaching importance to the nation, maintaining peace and achieving unity to add brilliance to the June 15 reunification era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It urged the need for the youth and students to strengthen the All-Korean Committee for Implementation of June 15 Joint Declaration, put their movement on a mass basis and take the lead in the struggle to achieve the great alliance against conservatism so as to foil the GNP's attempt to seize power in the "presidential elections" this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A lecture and speeches on the themes of "Understanding of the Songun Policy" and "History of the U.S. Imperialists' Aggression", etc. were given at the meeting.

Rodong Sinmun on Revolutionary Traits of Korean People 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 4 (KCNA) -- Rodong Sinmun Sunday dedicates an article to the 15th anniversary of the publication of Kim Jong Il's famous work "Let Us Cement the Single-minded Unity and Give Full Play to the Korean Nation-First Spirit".
 The work, published on Feb. 4, Juche 81 (1992), serves as a militant banner which helps all the Party members and other working people thoroughly preserve the Juche character and national identity in the revolution and construction and triumphantly advance the cause of socialism with high pride and honor of being members of Kim Il Sung's nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The nation-first spirit is the ideological and mental source to achieve the independent development and prosperity of the country and the nation, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary traits of the Korean people fully demonstrating the dignity and honor of the nation is found in that they are carrying out the revolution and construction their own way with a high degree of national self-respect and preserving the national ways in all fields of social life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also manifested in that they are devoting all their wisdom and efforts to achieving the prosperity of the nation, rallied closer around Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 High dignity and honor of Kim Il Sung's nation are now being displayed all over the world and the Korean people are boundlessly proud of being the most revolutionary and independent people. This is the precious fruition of the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 History and the reality clearly show that the Songun policy is, indeed, a sacred patriotic banner and a treasured sword for the national prosperity to honor the country and fully display the dignity and glory of the nation.

U.S.-Japan Tie-ups for Distortion of History under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 4 (KCNA) -- The United States has used as a textbook for middle school students a Japanese novel "Story of Yoko" which describes as if the Korean people "maltreated" Japanese in the closing years of the Japanese imperialist colonial rule over Korea, according to CBS of south Korea.
 This proves that the U.S. has joined Japan in distorting the historical facts and deliberately insulting the Korean nation, says Minju Joson Sunday in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush bellicose group is trying hard to provoke a war against the DPRK in a bid to swallow up not only south Korea but the whole of Korea by force of arms. The reactionaries of Japan, who revived with the help of the U.S., are also raising their sword of reinvasion, crying out for "sanctions and pressure" on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For their common interests, the U.S. covers up Japan's crime-woven past by misleading public opinion and instigates Japan to act a shock brigade in realizing its design for aggression on the DPRK. That is why the U.S. has connived and fostered the Japanese reactionaries' distortion of history in conspiracy with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and Japan should put a ban on the use of the novel and remove its copies at once, clearly understanding the gravity of the development, and apologize to the Korean nation for insulting it.

Policy for Hegemony Bound to Go Bust 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 4 (KCNA) -- The imperialists are pursuing a high-handed policy but it is bound to go bankrupt, stresses Rodong Sinmun Sunday.
 It is the truth of history that the unreasonable and reactionary policy has short wings and is doomed to failure as it hamstrings the desire and will of humankind for independence and goes against the trend of the times toward independence, the daily says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the common desire of peoples around the world to build a new peaceful world free from aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history has advanced and developed through vigorous and persistent struggle of the people aspiring after independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. exercise of high-handed policy is a very dangerous act of going against history and peace as it is contrary to the desire and will of humankind for independence and progress. It is a height of folly to calculate that it is possible to dominate the world by force of arms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the countries have equal rights as members of the international community and they are obliged to abide by the rules and principles of international relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. tramples down other countries by military force as they have differing ideology and system and do not obey it. This is a wanton violation of international law and an act of going against history obstructive to the sound development of the international relations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 High-handed policy can not work in the present world and it is bound to go bust. This is evidenced by the fact that the U.S. finds itself in a hard corner at present. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Iraq is now a mantrap for the U.S. imperialists. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The imperialists' persistent high-handed policy for hegemony would only reveal their vulnerability, not mightiness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The more desperately they resort to high-handed and arbitrary practices, the more clearly their reactionary and vulnerable nature is revealed, accelerating their international isolation and destruction.

Removal of Reactionary Conservatives in S. Korea Urged 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 4 (KCNA) -- The reactionary conservatives of south Korea such as the Grand National Party should be excluded from the nation promptly as they are the filth of the present era and the most hackneyed force seeking only luxury and glory with dependence on the outside forces.
 Rodong Sinmun Sunday makes this demand in a by-lined article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The above-said right-wing conservatives are shabby traitors who stoop to any treachery to live in comfort and luxury, indifferent to the interests of the nation, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Daily growing are the desire and demand of the south Korean people from all walks of life to eradicate all sorts of the old and ensure social justice through a campaign for progress and reforms. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Only a handful of reactionary conservatives are persisting in the old, viciously blocking the social progress and reform. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A majority of south Korean people have demanded the repeal of the "National Security Law" (NSL) and the withdrawal of the U.S. troops. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 But the conservatives stand against the forces for progress and reform, asserting that the repeal of the NSL means "self-disarmament" and it will "destroy the nature of system." Meanwhile, they call for "reinforced alliance" with the U.S., arguing that south Korea and the U.S. should keep step with each other and the forces urging the withdrawal of the U.S. forces from south Korea regarded as "pro-north".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans have hailed the June 15 joint declaration and the idea of "By our nation itself", regarding them as a landmark for national reunification in the present era. However, the GNP and other conservatives of south Korea are dead-set against them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality clearly shows that the desire of the south Korean people for progress and reform and all the Koreans' wish for peace and independent reunification on the Korean Peninsula can not be realized as long as such pro-U.S. conservatives are left intact.

U.S., Japan Hit for Distortion of History
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 4 (KCNA) -- The United States has used as a textbook for middle school students the history novel written by descendant of a Japanese war criminal which seriously defiles the Korean nation. Such behavior is an intolerable mockery of the Korean nation and an act of going against justice, conscience, truth and history that is little short of painting evil as good and an assailant as a victim.
 A spokesman for the History Society of the DPRK stressed this in a statement on Sunday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As for the novel, it is a book made up of falsehood and fabrication quite contrary to the then historical backgrounds and facts, the statement said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Noting that the book describes that Japan occupied Korea through such legitimate process as the "Taft-Katsura Agreement," the statement cited data to prove that such claim is a brigandish sophism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It further said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. application of this distorted novel as a textbook is a wrong behavior against common sense, and it is designed to cover up the Japanese imperialists' bloody crime-woven past and mislead the public opinion to use them as a shock brigade in executing aggression and war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. should immediately stop such behavior and, together with Japan, remove copies of the novel and textbooks and make an apology for it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The authorities and the Grand National Party of south Korea have turned aside from the case, failing to make even a word of protest, the statement pointed out, saying: Historians and other people from different circles in south Korea should resolutely denounce the U.S. and Japan for their distortion of history and nexus for aggression.

Works of Peerless Great Men Disseminated in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- A seminar and a lecture on famous works of Kim Jong Il were held by the Ethiopian Youth Study Group of the Juche Idea and at Mongolian State University on Jan. 22 and 23 on the occasion of his birthday.
 The chairman of the Ethiopian group said at the seminar on the work "Let Us Defend and Further Glorify Our Own Socialism under the Uplifted Banner of the Juche Idea" that socialism of Korea is a people-centered socialism based on the Juche idea fathered by President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is thanks to Kim Jong Il and the great idea that the DPRK has advanced along the road chosen by itself, not yielding to the moves of the world reactionaries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-chairman of the Mongolian Mt. Paektu Association for Independent Development said, before his lecture explaining the work "Socialism Is What Keeps Our People Alive," that the Korean people have made long strides, meeting all challenges of the imperialist allied forces, under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the Nepal Institute for the Juche Studies donated famous works of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il to a middle school on Jan. 19. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The vice-chairman of the institute and other figures said at the presentation ceremony that the works would help the Nepalese people to have a better understanding of the Korean people who always emerge victorious in showdown with the imperialist allied forces under the Songun politics of Kim Jong Il. In particular, they greatly encourage all the Nepalese people in their efforts to build an independent, peaceful and prosperous, new society, the speakers added.

Pyongyang City Water System Improved
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- The project for renovating the Pyongyang City water system has been completed.
 This will help ensure the production and supply of drinking water on a higher level on the basis of modern equipment and information means. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A ceremony for the completion of the project was held on the spot on Friday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present were Minister of City Management Choe Jong Gon, Vice-Chairman of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries Jon Hyon Chan who is chairman of the DPRK-Kuwait Friendship Association, Vice-Chairman of the Pyongyang City People's Committee Han Hyon Sop, other officials concerned and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A visiting delegation of the Kuwait Fund for Arab Economic Development headed by its Deputy Director General Hesham Al-Waqayan was on hand. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The minister of City Management made a speech at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then the participants went round the renovated water system.

Moves for Revival of Fascist Dictatorship Blasted in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- The authorities of the Hapchon County Office in South Kyongsang Province, south Korea, decided to call a park in the county "Ilhae Park," which is the nickname of traitor Chun Doo Hwan. In this connection, public circles of south Korea have strongly denounced it as a move to revive the fascist dictatorship, according to a press report.
 The Kwangju-South Jolla Provincial Measure Committee against Ilhae Park, consisting of ten civic and public organizations in Kwangju including the Association of May 18 Men of Merits for Democracy and Bereaved Families, issued a statement on Jan. 29 at which it said that the county office authorities' decision to rename the park in "memory of" the traitor is as good as an act of going back to the past era of fascist dictatorship and stabbing a dagger into all the people desirous of democracy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement contended that traitor Chun Doo Hwan is a dictator and murderer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean Journalists Association in a statement on Jan. 30 said that Chun, a military dictator, is the chief culprit of the Kwangju massacre and suppression of the press and a kingpin of illicit fortune, adding that it is nonsensical to "honor" such guy.

No to Revival of Dark Era in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- On Jan. 23 the south Korean Court declared not guilty the eight persons who had been sentenced to capital punishment on charges of violation of "emergency measure No.1," "National Security Law" and "the anti-communist law" and "conspiracy of a rebellion" after drawing the conclusion that the case of the "Committee for the Reconstruction of the People's Revolutionary Party" was faked up through harsh acts including torture. This court ruling once again brought to light the "Yusin" dictator's cruel killings of innocent people. 
 Minju Joson Saturday says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  The case was a conspiratorial case in which the dictator used again the already disclosed case of "the People's Revolutionary Party" in a bid to stay long in power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As those who were killed on charges of involvement in the above-said case were declared not guilty more than 30 years later, the Grand National Party of south Korea (GNP) has become the target of public criticism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean people are now strongly demanding the GNP and the daughter of the "Yusin" dictator, in particular, come out to apologize for the anti-communist cases faked up in the past period of fascist dictatorship. It is quite a just assertion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Nevertheless, the GNP gentry are only keen to grab power, far from uttering even a word of apology.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If they are allowed to come to power, they will bring no doubt disastrous consequences to south Korea. It is as clear as a pikestaff that there will rage the same whirlwind of fascist tyranny and confrontation as what was under the "Yusin" dictatorship and more cases similar to the above-mentioned case will be fabricated to kill innocent people on false charges. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the only way of preventing the revival of the dark rule of fascist dictatorship to deter the descendants of the dictator from usurping power again.

Anti-DPRK Outbursts of GNP Representative Blasted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- The representative of the Grand National Party of south Korea called a "New Year press conference" on Jan. 26, asserting it is allegedly aimed at exercising the "right to refute" the "New Year address" made by the chief executive.
 He went so impudent as to serve a "warning" to the north, letting loose a spate of balderdash that "the north's nukes and missiles pose a threat to the Korean Peninsula and the global peace" and "it is necessary to urge the north to dismantle its nukes and opt for peace as early as possible." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A news analyst of Rodong Sinmun Saturday observes in this regard: The representative of the GNP at the "New Year press conference" began with slandering and attacking not only the authorities of south Korea but forces for progressive reforms and, not content with this, went the lengths of pulling up and admonishing the DPRK. This was nothing but a spate of vituperation and provocative remarks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 When looking back on history, peace on the Korean Peninsula has been threatened by the U.S. imperialist aggression troops and the south Korean warlike forces, the conservative forces opposed to reunification including the GNP in actuality. The above-said U.S. aggressor forces, equipped with all types of ultra-modern weapons of mass destruction including nukes, have watched for a chance to invade the north, pursuant to the U.S. policy of aggression towards the DPRK, and those trigger-happy forces of south Korea have followed the road of confrontation with the north and war, backed by the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK has built up the nuclear deterrent despite all hardships, guided by the will of all its servicepersons and people for self-defence because it is possible to counter the enemy equipped with nukes with nukes only. It is a reality that the majority of the south Koreans agree with this and feel proud of the north's nuclear deterrent. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The responsibility for compelling the DPRK to have access to nukes also rests with the GNP, a war servant of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Had not the military dictators who ruled south Korea before the GNP allowed the U.S. introduction of nuclear weapons to it, the issue of the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula would not have cropped up and had not they permitted the U.S. interference and domination over south Korea while keeping its occupation forces after faking up a "resolution on opposing the withdrawal of the U.S. forces", the independent and peaceful reunification of the peninsula would already have come true. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now is the June 15 era for reunification. To reject pro-north people at a time when the north and the south should get reconciled and cooperate with each other to solve the issue of peace and promote co-existence and co-prosperity is like a declaration of war as it is an open negation of the north and a declaration of continued confrontation with it and a revelation of an intention to scrap the June 15 joint declaration and put an end to the June 15 era. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What the GNP seeks is to keep everything in Korea divided by perpetuating the territorial division and deepening the social division, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is none other than the GNP gentry who are so weak as to cling to the coattails of the aggression forces, taken aback by a mere word of independence uttered by someone. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is an inveterate habit of the GNP group to depend on outsiders. It feels no shame as its days are numbered. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the final analysis, the GNP gentry staged the above-said charade in a bid to win popularity under the pretext of exercising the "right to refute" the above-mentioned "New Year address" but it only brought into bolder relief their true colors as traitors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is clear from the recent press conference that the GNP has finally betrayed its ulterior intention and unsheathed its sword to hurt not only the north but the forces supporting the June 15 joint declaration. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is nothing but a political cartoon and an ugly conduct for the GNP, the worst party of traitors in history, to pull up others.

Rodong Sinmun on Immortal Feats of Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- President Kim Il Sung conducted energetic activities for global independence, regarding it as his lifelong aims and mission to accomplish this cause, and thus performed undying exploits for the times and history that will remain long.
 Rodong Sinmun Saturday says this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Basing himself on the intrinsic qualities of the popular masses regarding independence as their life and soul, the President gave a clear exposition of all the theoretical and practical matters arising in their efforts to hew out the destiny of their country and nation independently and make a new history of independence under the banner of independence, the article notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He perfectly expounded the principled requirements, tasks and strategy and tactics for global independence and led the revolutionary people around the world to the struggle for their materialization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He worked heart and soul to defend and develop socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He proved in a scientific way the validity and truth of socialism and the necessity of its final victory while giving a perfect exposition of all principles and theoretical and practical matters arising in the building of socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also clarified the idea that the world's peace-loving people should continue to intensify the movement for peace against imperialism and war with the revolutionary vigilance, and evidently indicated its practical ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to beef up the anti-imperialist and independent forces, he paid great efforts to strengthening the international support and solidarity with the struggles of countries and nations advocating independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After all, the common struggle purpose and ideal of the progressive countries and nations and the co-relations between them were clarified by the President. This made it possible to boost support and solidarity among the independent and progressive countries and expand the anti-imperialist and independent forces.

U.S. Hit for Using Distorted History Novel as Textbook
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, February 3 (KCNA) -- The United States has used as a textbook for middle school students the book authored by Japanese, a descendant of a war criminal. The book distorts the historical facts, seriously defiling the Korean nation's dignity.
 In this regard, a spokesman for the Central Committee of the Union of Educationists and Men of Culture of Korea released a statement on Saturday dismissing it as an intolerable insult and mockery of the Korean nation and an act of going against history and justice that is little short of painting evil as good and an assailant as a victim. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The statement said: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The book "Story of Yoko" is an autobiography-novel written by Kawashima Yoko, daughter of a Japanese war criminal. She was 11 years old at the time of the defeat of the Japanese imperialism. The book describes as if Koreans maltreated and sexually assaulted Japanese on their way to the Japan proper. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It also asserts that Japan occupied Korea, which was subject to the scramble of big powers, through such legitimate process as the "Taft-Katsura Agreement." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. application of this distorted novel as textbook for students is designed to cover up the past crimes of Japan and mislead the public opinion to use it as a shock brigade in executing aggression and war. This brings into bolder relief the truth that the U.S. and Japan have been conspiring to launch aggression on Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All the Koreans in the north and the south and abroad should never allow the U.S. and Japan, which cruelly violated the destiny of the Korean nation through their nexus for aggression on it a century ago, to run amuck to invade it again while burying their crime-woven past into oblivion.
